a treatment. A patient’s glucose level should not exceed
a critical level (yupper
, upper threshold) where she will
experience hyperglycemia. Nor should a patient’s glucose
level fall below a critical level (ylower, lower threshold)
where she will experience hypoglycemia (Bode et al.,
2005). The thresholds yupper and ylower are defined a priori
